commit.message:
Correct typo

Thanks to Robert Rothenberg.

For: https://rt.cpan.org/Ticket/Display.html?id=152557

CPAN version 0.008

Bump $VERSION; update Changes file.

Explicitly skip certain tests if FCR not installed

Certain CPANtesters rigs are testing with PERL_AUTHOR_TESTING=1 set to
true.  This was causing spurious failures when test blocks that I
expected to be skipped were actually run and a 'die' condition was
encountered.

Example: http://www.cpantesters.org/cpan/report/25107c84-7429-1014-9995-b164e19d8e1a

This commit modifies 4 locations in 3 test files to require that certain
blocks only be run if *both* PERL_AUTHOR_TESTING=true and
File::Copy::Reduced is installed.
trigger
Start preparing Changes for next release

Add encoding directive to POD

To accommodate non-ASCII character in contributor's name.

For: https://rt.cpan.org/Ticket/Display.html?id=150222.

Clarification of 0.007 changes

There was no functional change in module; only touch-ups in test files.

CPAN version 0.007

Update dates in prep for CPAN release.

Because of the extensive use of calendar dates in the POD in
lib/File/Copy/Recursive/Reduced.pm, the use of my bump_version.pl script
is overkill here.  Hence, removing .version_info.pl from distribution.

Convert path to canonical path on Windows

File::Find returns path with forward slashes on Windows
so we need to convert to canonical path before comparing
